quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  9,14,"Combat them, so that Allah may punish them at your hands and disgrace them and support you against them and heal the chests of a believing people"
  9,15,"and remove the rage in their hearts. And Allah grants repentance and accepts it from whomever He wills. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise."
  9,16,"Or do you think that you will be left alone without Allah identifying{1}those of you who strive and take no confidants apart from Allah and His Messenger and the believers? And Allah is All-Aware of what you do.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘knowing’.
  9,17,"Never was it befitting for the polytheists to attend Allah’s <span class=""h"">mosques<sup foot_note=""80152"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>while professing their denial. Those—their deeds were nullified, and in the Fire they abide."
  9,18,"Surely, Allah’s mosques can only be attended by one who has attained faith in Allah and the Last Day and has established the prayer and brought{1}the purifying charity{2}and feared none but Allah, for hopefully those will become of the guided ones.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.|2:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.
  9,19,"Do you equate <span class=""h"">giving water</span><span class=""h"">to pilgrims and maintaining<sup foot_note=""80155"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>the Inviolable Mosque with<i class=""s"">(the deeds of) </i>whoever have attained faith in Allah and the Last Day and have striven in the way of Allah? They are not equal before Allah. And Allah does not guide the unjust people."
  9,20,"Those who attained faith and emigrated and strove in the way of Allah with their wealths and themselves are of a higher degree<i class=""s"">(of rank) </i>before Allah, and it is those who are the triumphant ones."
